@NODE INSTALLATION "Installation"
@{" Introduction " Link INTRODUCTION}@{" Disclaimer " Link DISCLAIMER}@{fg shine}@{bg text} Install @{fg text}@{bg back}@{" Config " Link CONFIG}@{" History " Link HISTORY}@{" Thanks " Link THANX}@{" Bugs? " Link BUGS}

                           FullDed Installation.

          Installation is as simple as can be, just do like this:

          1. Rename Doors:Ded/Ded to Doors:Ded/Ded.org (Only for backup)

          2. Copy FullDed to Doors:Ded/

          3. Rename FullDed to Ded

          4. Copy FullDed.doc to Doors:Ded/

          5. Copy FullDed.txt to Doors:Ded/

          6. Copy FullDed.config to Doors:Ded/

          7. That's it!

          If you are using DedDiz or DizFix, do like this:

          1. Rename Doors:Ded/Ded_xeno to Doors:Ded/Ded.org (Only for backup)

          2. Copy FullDed to Doors:Ded/

          3. Rename FullDed to Ded_xeno

          4. Copy FullDed.doc to doors:Ded/

          5. Copy FullDed.txt to Doors:Ded/

          6. Copy FullDed.config to Doors:Ded/

          7. That's it!

   Please do *NOT* change this directory structure since these paths are
                               hardcoded !!

@ENDNODE

@NODE CONFIG "External Configuration Files"
@{" Introduction " Link INTRODUCTION}@{" Disclaimer " Link DISCLAIMER}@{" Install " Link INSTALLATION}@{fg shine}@{bg text} Config @{fg text}@{bg back}@{" History " Link HISTORY}@{" Thanks " Link THANX}@{" Bugs? " Link BUGS}

                       FullDed Configuration Files.

 Doors:Ded/FullDed.Config
 ------------------------

;
; Configuration file for Fullscreen Ded v2.0 (c) 1996 HAL9000 Media.
;
; (This file has to be in Doors:Ded/)
;
;Write in upper or lower case as you want, and in any order. But if you
;leave some option out, the default will be user.

TOP=4,4			;4,4 is default.
FILE=3,56		;3,56 is default.
FREE=17,69		;17,69 is default.
WRAP=18,69		;18,69 is default.
INS=19,69		;19,69 is default.

;Usage: Top=y,x
;
;This is the top of the editor screen.
;If you make you own screen, then you must fix so that the editor writes at
;the right place. Use you ansieditor to get the pos, or just test ;)
;
;Max 99,99 But all cords over 30,79 is STUPID ;)
;(Even 30,79 is stupid... hehe)


ON=ON			;ON is default.
OFF=OFF			;OFF is default.
LINE=LINE		;LINE is default.

;Usage: ON/OFF/LINE=TEXT
;
;Text to use after insert, wordwrap and freehand. (Max 8 chars!)
;Can be used for translation.

CFILE=3			;3 is default.
CON=3			;3 is default.
COFF=3			;3 is default.
CLINE=3			;3 is default.
CMAIN=3			;3 is default.

;Usage: CFILE/CON/COFF/CLINE/CMAIN=ansi color number (Max 1 char!)
;
;CFILE Filename color
;CON 'ON' color
;COFF 'OFF' color
;CLINE 'LINE' color
;CMAIN Msgtext and cursur color.
;
;Just to make it look nice with your color config.

DEFINS=OFF		;default is OFF
DEFWRAP=ON		;default is ON
DEFFREE=ON		;default is ON

;DEFINS, Insertmode off/line when enter the door.
;DEFINS=ON will be the same as writing LINE since total insert is not yet
;working... :(
;
;DEFWRAP, wordwrap on/off, if the door will wrap words from the begining.
;DEFFREE, freehand edit on/off...
;
;All TABs will be made into space, lines will end when it reads a ;
;
;You can have space/tab in the begining of a line if you want to.
;


 Doors:Ded/FullDed.doc
 ---------------------

Just a textfile that user can use as online help, you are free to
edit/translate this file as you want.


 Doors:Ded/FullDed.txt
 ---------------------

The screenlayout, remember to edit the cords in config file if you change
the filename or option posion. And this file *MUST* have LF+CR at end of
line!

@ENDNODE

